The paper deals with the mixing time of a random walk in a polytope, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves optimization and sampling, which are relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The use of log-barrier and interior point methods suggests a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
